This wasnâ€™t just about cutting grass; it was an ode to survival etched in every swing of the weathered scythe. An elderly woman, a silhouette against the backdrop of rolling hills and rustic charm, maneuvering a tool almost as ancient as her. The rhythmic cadence of the blade carving through the grass sang a ballad of resilience that transcended the boundaries of time. It was as if the scythe itself held the secrets of a thousand lifetimes, whispered through the hands of those who had faced hardship head-on. In the heart of Romanian villages, where the air is heavy with the tales of survival and shared history, the elders cultivate more than just crops. Our grandma, with her face etched in lines of laughter and wisdom, was a guardian of a fading dialect â€“ the language of resilience, of grit. The scythe, a silent protagonist in this tale, became a bridge connecting the elderly to the present, a tool passed down like an heirloom, carrying the weight of memories in its worn blade.  As she honed that blade with a special stone and cleaned it with freshly cut grass, it wasnâ€™t just about maintaining a tool; it was a ritual, a communion with a way of life that had weathered storms and stood resilient against the test of time. Could you do it? 90 years old and still making the youngsters look like amateurs. In a tucked-away corner of Romania, where time seemed to have frozen in a poignant dance with tradition, I stumbled upon a living testament to the indomitable spirit of life. A grandma, a matriarch in the heart of her village, carving poetry with a scythe in her â€œbatatura,â€ the courtyard that cradled generations of stories. This wasnâ€™t just about cutting grass; it was an ode to survival etched in every swing of the weathered scythe. An elderly woman, a silhouette against the backdrop of rolling hills and rustic charm, maneuvering a tool almost as ancient as her. The rhythmic cadence of the blade carving through the grass sang a ballad of resilience that transcended the boundaries of time. It was as if the scythe itself held the secrets of a thousand lifetimes, whispered through the hands of those who had faced hardship head-on. In the heart of Romanian villages, where the air is heavy with the tales of survival and shared history, the elders cultivate more than just crops. Our grandma, with her face etched in lines of laughter and wisdom, was a guardian of a fading dialect â€“ the language of resilience, of grit. The scythe, a silent protagonist in this tale, became a bridge connecting the elderly to the present, a tool passed down like an heirloom, carrying the weight of memories in its worn blade. As she honed that blade with a special stone and cleaned it with freshly cut grass, it wasnâ€™t just about maintaining a tool; it was a ritual, a communion with a way of life that had weathered storms and stood resilient against the test of time. I'll be reviewing running routes from all over the world. Running has been my daily ritual for the past ten years, helping me through some tough times. For the last fourteen months, I've been on an incredible journey across sixteen countries, and no matter where I am, running is a must for me. However, I've noticed a lack of detailed information about running routes, especially in less-traveled locations. That's why I'm creating a series of videos reviewing hundreds of different runs from various places around the globe. In each video, I'll share insights about the location and the route itself. I'll only feature routes I'd personally recommendâ€”whether they're fast, flat, and long, or a challenging uphill with breathtaking views.  These routes aren't just great runs; they're also fantastic ways to explore new places. If any of the routes catch your eye, just comment "run" on the video, and I'll share the Strava route with you. You don't need to be super fit or fast to try these routesâ€”I'm not! I do enjoy long distances, so you'll find everything from 5Ks to marathons in my reviews. About Serval Wildlife and the animals taken from their website: "Our sanctuary is over 1000 acres, prepared in phases and in accordance with the needs of our animals 50 acres at a time. Animals are ethically obtained from zoos & injured animals from the wild with the aim of instilling natural behaviors and eventually rehabilitating them into the wild with the assistance of TAWA and TAWIRI. The animals that reside within our wildlife sanctuary are owned by the Tanzanian Government and often brought to us by TAWA as orphans or injured wildlife. We treat and train our animals to prepare them for release into their natural habitat within TANAPA protected parks. Our wildlife sanctuary also doubles as an endangered species reintroduction platform to translocate animals to parts of its natural range where populations have significantly declined or been lost. Aiming to establish a viable population within translocated areas. Our most recent animals for release are our lions. Brought to us from other zoos due to being rejected by their mother at a very young age. Upon arrival these animals were in poor condition, we have trained them and nursed them back to health. ğŸ¥ In our latest video, we dive deep into the remarkable story of the Mothers of Plaza de Mayo, a group of courageous women who stood up against Argentina's military dictatorship in a powerful display of resilience and love. During a time when gathering in public was severely restricted and cultural expressions like tango and carnival were banned, these brave mothers found a way to protest peacefully. They gathered every Thursday in front of the Casa Rosada, creatively circumventing restrictions by walking arm in arm in circles to demand answers about their disappeared children. Their struggle is a poignant reminder of the power of peaceful protest and the enduring strength of maternal love. Despite facing the same grim fate as their children, the Mothers of Plaza de Mayo remain a symbol of resistance and hope, continuing their demonstrations to this day. Their story is not just history; it's a call to remember the sacrifices made for human rights and justice. Watch the full story and be inspired by their unwavering determination. Let's honor these incredible women by spreading their story far and wide. ğŸ•Šï¸ #MothersOfPlazaDeMayo #PeacefulProtest #SocialJustice #TrueStories #Inspiration #MoreThanJustFood #BuenosAiresHistory #NeverForget #FoodTour #HiddenGems #TravelAuthentic #HumanRights #Argentina #AsadoAdventure #FoodTravelGoals #TravelTips #ArgentinaUnveiled #HiddenGems #FoodAndNeighborhoodTour #ArgentinaTravel #MustSeeBuenosAires #PalermoSoho #buenosairesfoodtour #PalermoSoHoFoodTour #BuenosAiresFoodTour #FoodieTravel #TravelGram #exploreargentina #HistoryBuff #Culture #FoodandHistoryTour #EthicalTravel

Sometimes I still have to pinch myself when we find dreamy park-ups like this one ğŸŒ¿âœ¨ Sustainable travel looks different for everyone, and it can feel challenging to choose eco-friendly options when youâ€™re on a tight budget. Before we had the van, even the cheapest hotels were out of reach thanks to inflated prices, and most of our money went towards taking the train instead of flying. In fact, I can count the holidays Iâ€™ve had in the last decade on one hand. Our only real option was the occasional multi-day hike, and even then, much of the time was spent navigating bus routes just to get across the country. One of the things I love the most about travelling in our little home on wheels is that it lets us contribute more directly to local economies. The money we save on accommodation goes to local bookshops, cozy cafÃ©s, and the occasional tourist spot to help maintain natural areas. Plus, working remotely means we can schedule our adventures with less hassle and earn money on the road ğŸš We often get questions about wild camping in the van, and yes â€” itâ€™s totally doable! In our last 6 months of van life, we havenâ€™t stayed at a single campsite. Our strategy during the busier months of the year has been to hike in the mornings whenever we can, and drive in the afternoons to snag the perfect spot before anyone else. Solar power has been pretty much limitless in the summer (though weâ€™re getting more mindful now as autumn sets in), and for water, we just visit campsites on the way and offer a small donation. Full day Tour  From $55pp Depart from Cape Town in a luxury air-conditioned coach and head directly to the Franschhoek valley to join the Franschhoek hop-on hop-off wine tram and bus. The Franschhoek Wine Tram offers two hop-on hop-off lines (clockwise & anti-clockwise), each visiting various wine estates in the Franschhoek Valley. Enjoy transportation to each wine estate every hour by a combination of tram and tram-buses around the loop. Each stop is at a different wine estate, allowing you to hop on and hop off at any of the estates. The tram or tram passes each stop once an hour, so you can explore at your convenience to move from one estate to the next. Head back to the Franschhoek Wine Tram station for your transfer back to Cape Town You can select from five different routes, each of which takes you to various wine estates that highlight different aspects of the Franschhoek Valley. With the Hop-on Hop-off experience, you have the freedom to design and organize your own day. You can decide how much time you want to spend at each location (within the line's schedule, naturally), where you want to dine, where you want to enjoy some wine, and which activities you'd like to participate in. Your adventure commences at either the Franschhoek Terminal or the Groot Drakenstein Terminal, depending on the route you've chosen. While you wait for your journey to commence, you can grab a coffee, savor a beignet, and explore our selection of merchandise. Starting from the terminals, you'll be transported through the designated stops on your chosen route using a combination of double-decker trams and open-air tram-buses, providing you with the flexibility to disembark at your convenience. info@safaricapetownza.com +27 66 1854882 +27 87 265 6420 #safaricapetowntoursza #safaricapetownza #capetownsafari #Southafrica #dreamholiday #sustainabletravel #explore #tourguidelife #luxurynature #exploreafrica #bestvacations #loveanimals #impactonwildlife #ExperienceTravel #capetowntourism #CapeTownSafari #capewinelands #wineenthusiast

Located in the stunning Namib Desert, Camp Sossus offers an intimate and eco-friendly safari experience, where luxury meets sustainability. Nestled within a private reserve near the iconic red dunes of Sossusvlei, the camp provides breathtaking views of rugged desert landscapes, endless starry skies, and rich wildlife, including oryx, springbok, and the elusive desert-adapted animals. With only a handful of exclusive tented suites, Camp Sossus is designed for those seeking serenity and a deep connection with nature. Each suite blends seamlessly into the environment, offering all the comforts of modern living while maintaining a minimal ecological footprint. From sunrise hikes up the towering dunes to sundowners in the desert, every moment at Camp Sossus is an immersion into the raw beauty of Namibia. Perfect for nature lovers and adventure seekers, Camp Sossus invites you to explore one of the worldâ€™s most unique and otherworldly environments in unmatched style and tranquility. #campsossus #namibdesert #ecoluxury #sossusvlei #NamibiaSafari #desertretreat #sustainabletravel #naturelover #bucketlistadventures #adventure #safari #africansafari #luxurytravel #namibia #desertsafari #bucketlisttravel #sailadventuresafaris

The most devastating hike Iâ€™ve been onğŸ‘‡ğŸ¼ ğŸ“Location at the endğŸ“ Iâ€™ll be completely honest, Iâ€™ve never really been a huge advocate for sustainable travel. I respected people who practiced it but I didnâ€™t do anything myself. ğŸ˜¢ I always thought things like: â€˜How can me giving an airline an extra Â£2 to offset carbon emissions really help the environment?â€™ And so I did nothing ğŸ¤·â€â™€ï¸ But this hike really opened my eyes! It was devastating. It was kind of like walking through a haunted forest, completely scarred by the forest fires that ravaged it in summer last year. â˜€ï¸  Several of the gorges had be completely closed due to tree fall and many of the hiking trails were surrounded by debris and dead trees. ğŸŒ² These fires needed 400 firefighters to extinguish . Over 1200 hectares of forest was burned and hundreds of people were evacuated. ğŸ”¥  Yes, I know that forest fires are a natural part of many ecosystems, playing a crucial role in clearing dead vegetation and allowing new growth to thrive.ğŸŒ³ But, thereâ€™s no denying that human activities, from climate change to careless actions, contribute to the increasing frequency of wildfires. Look at Rhodes this year! And Hawaii! ğŸ˜­ It made me realize how vital it is for us to protect our natural world. Imagine the impact on the planet if this continues? Imagine if every hike you went on had views like this?ğŸ˜« So, here are a few ways to practice sustainable travel: - Use efficient modes of transport. Trains are much more environmentally friendly than taxis. ğŸšŠ  - Use reusable water bottles. Saves on plastic and itâ€™s just more practical! - Spend in local communities and support local businesses. ğŸ’°  - Explore hidden gems. While everyone is rushing off to popular cities or islands, why not try to find hidden gems? I often find they make for a nicer travel experience, especially with the lack of crowds. ğŸ’  Trust me when I say this, but you wonâ€™t realise how bad things could get until you see it with your own eyes. ğŸ˜­ ğŸ“Location: Hrensko, Czechia ğŸ“ âœ¨SAVEâœ¨ this post of you found it helpful and letâ€™s work together to protect our environment ğŸŒ  FOLLOW @adventuresofalicee for more travels, outdoors, and inspiration âœˆï¸ #forestfire #devastation #outdoorlovers #lovehiking #visitczechrepublic #hrensko #sustainabletravel #protecttheplanet

Rahasia Kelezatan Kuliner di Jantung Hutan Tanjung Puting Menjelajahi Taman Nasional Tanjung Puting bukan hanya tentang petualangan di alam liar, tapi juga tentang menikmati kelezatan kuliner yang tak terduga. Di atas kelotok, para juru masak handal Lookorangutan siap memanjakan lidah Anda dengan hidangan istimewa. Bukan sekadar juru masak biasa, mereka tergabung dalam Perkumpulan Asosiasi Chef Tanjung Puting, yang rutin berlatih untuk menyajikan: Menu bergizi dan seimbang: Pagi, siang, sore, dan snack, semua tersusun dengan pertimbangan nutrisi dan selera. Variasi menu: Menu Indonesia, Asia, dan Barat tersedia, dengan pilihan vegetarian, rendah garam, dan tanpa MSG. Pesan khusus: Lobster, udang galah, dan hidangan mewah lainnya dapat disiapkan sesuai permintaan. Pengalaman istimewa: Lebih dari 6 orang tamu akan ditemani 2 juru masak untuk memastikan kelezatan setiap hidangan. Hawa hutan dan panorama alam yang memesona akan menambah kenikmatan setiap suapan. You will notice that the elephant in front looks like it is missing his tusks. However they are broken in a fight with another elephant - not poaching in this case! ğŸ˜ When I first posted this video it went viral with so many questions about the tusks. Thankfully this elephant was not the victim of poaching but others are not so lucky.  As today is #WorldElephantDay, I wanted to highlight that  Elephant poaching for ivory has destroyed 90% of elephant populations in the past century!  Ivory, found in elephant tusks, has been an incredibly lucrative industry for centuries, often seen as a status symbol. Due to massive illegal poaching in the 1970s and 1980s to satisfy the demand for ivory, particularly in Asia, around 90% of Africaâ€™s elephant population has been wiped out in the past century.  Although many countries have now banned the ivory trade, more than 20,000 elephants are still killed every year to meet the continuing demand in places like China and Japan. #amboselinationalpark #elephantsoftiktok #kenyansafari #uniqueplaces #placestovisit #adventuretravel #bucketlisttrip #wildlifevideos #wildlifefacts #wildlifeonearth #sustainabletravel #wildlifephotographer #safariphotography #safari #wildlifetiktok #africansafari #didyouknow  #wildlifetiktokers #elephantlovers #elephantfacts #elephanttiktok #amboselielephants #travelblogger #didyouknowfacts #kenyasafari #elephantlove #elephantğŸ˜ #elephantlover Amboseli | Elephants | wildlife | amboseli national park | kenya | safari | facts | africa | african wildlife | african elephants | did you know | friendship | inspirational | motivational

Viva con Agua is a non-profit organization that advocates for access to clean drinking water, sanitation, and hygiene, commonly referred to by the acronym WASH. Founded in 2006 in St. Pauli, Hamburg, Germany, by former FC St. Pauli footballer Benjamin Adrion, Viva con Agua has grown significantly over the years. The organizationâ€™s primary objective is to ensure that all people worldwide have access to clean drinking water. The approach of Viva con Agua is notably inclusive and community-oriented, engaging volunteers, artists, musicians, and various other stakeholders in its campaigns and projects. This collaborative ethos is encapsulated in their slogan, â€œAll for Water - Water for All.â€ Through a mix of awareness campaigns, fundraising activities, and collaborations with other organizations, Viva con Agua supports water projects in countries facing severe water scarcity issues, such as Uganda, South Africa, and Nepal. In Nepal, Viva con Agua has contributed to improving the water and sanitation facilities in various communities, working closely with local partners to implement sustainable solutions tailored to the specific needs of each area. These projects not only focus on the physical provision of water but also on educational programs to promote hygiene practices, which are crucial for preventing waterborne diseases. The unique aspect of Viva con Aguaâ€™s work is its focus on the creative and joyful involvement of people. They use music, art, and sports to reach a broader audience and to raise awareness about the global water crisis in an engaging manner. This method has proven effective in spreading their message and mobilizing support across different cultures and communities. For travelers and trekking companies in Nepal, supporting or partnering with organizations like Viva con Agua can be a meaningful way to give back to the local communities they visit. It aligns well with responsible travel policies that emphasize sustainability and community welfare. ğŸŒŠ Today, we bid farewell to the incredible team at Viva con Agua, who are wrapping up their impactful water projects in Nepal. ğŸ‡³ğŸ‡µâœˆï¸ Your efforts in bringing clean water and hygiene education to our communities have made a lasting difference. Safe travels and keep spreading the joy and water for all! ğŸ’§ğŸŒ ğŸ”¹ #VivaConAgua #WaterForAll #NepalDeparture #CleanWater #GlobalGoals #SustainableTravel #ThankYouVivaConAgua #NepalTravelExperts #fyp #foryou #fypã‚· #foryoupage

Exploring the great outdoors is not just a physical journey; it's a transformative experience that nurtures the spirit, challenges the body, and creates lasting connections with others.  The Call of the Mountains The mountains stand as majestic sentinels, inviting adventurers to traverse their rugged paths. Whether itâ€™s a challenging ascent to a snow-capped peak or a leisurely hike through a sun-dappled valley, the mountains offer a diverse playground for all levels of adventurers. Each step on the trail brings with it a sense of discovery and wonder. The fresh, crisp air fills your lungs, invigorating your spirit, while the sounds of rustling leaves and chirping birds remind you of the beauty that surrounds you. The Joy of Exploration Exploring nature is an invitation to reconnect with the world around you. Every hike unveils hidden gemsâ€”serene lakes, vibrant wildflowers, and breathtaking viewpoints that take your breath away. The thrill of discovering new trails and uncharted territories ignites a sense of adventure that can only be found in the great outdoors. Whether youâ€™re navigating challenging terrains or enjoying a leisurely stroll, each moment spent in nature is a chance to reflect, recharge, and appreciate the wonders of the environment. Making New Friends One of the most enriching aspects of outdoor adventures is the opportunity to meet like-minded individuals who share your passion for exploration. Whether you join a hiking group, participate in a guided tour, or simply strike up a conversation at a scenic overlook, the mountains serve as a backdrop for forging new friendships. Sharing stories, laughter, and the occasional challenge fosters a sense of camaraderie that transcends the trails.  These connections often lead to unforgettable experiencesâ€”sharing meals under the stars, swapping gear tips, or encouraging one another during tough climbs. The bonds formed in nature are unique; they are built on shared experiences and a mutual appreciation for the beauty of the wild.  The Ripple Effect of Adventure As you venture into the mountains and connect with new friends, the impact of your exploration extends beyond the immediate experience. It inspires a sense of stewardship for the environment and a commitment to preserving these natural wonders for future generations. The stories shared around the campfire can spark a passion for conservation, encouraging you and your friends to advocate for the protection of the landscapes that have brought so much joy. My Conclusion Getting out there and exploring nature is not just about the thrill of adventure; itâ€™s about embracing the journey, discovering the beauty of the world, and forging connections with others who share your wanderlust. The mountains await, ready to unveil their secrets and offer a sense of belonging that resonates long after the trails have been conquered. So lace up your hiking boots, pack your backpack, and set forth on a journey of exploration, friendship, and unforgettable memories. The best ethical places to swim with whale sharks In the world ğŸŒ ğŸŒğŸŒğŸŒ Swimming with whale sharks can be an incredible experience, but it's essential to choose locations that prioritize ethical and sustainable interactions. Here are some of the best ethical places to swim with whale sharks around the world:  â€¢ Isla Holbox, Mexico:  â€¢ Whale shark season: June to September.  â€¢ Regulations limit the number of boats and swimmers to minimize stress on the animals.  â€¢ Guides are trained to ensure interactions are respectful and non-intrusive.  â€¢ Ningaloo Reef, Australia:  â€¢ Whale shark season: March to July.  â€¢ Strict regulations and permits control the number of visitors.  â€¢ Operators follow guidelines to ensure minimal impact on whale sharks.  â€¢ Gladden Spit, Belize:  â€¢ Whale shark season: April to June (around the full moon).  â€¢ Limited number of licenses for operators, ensuring controlled and respectful interactions.  â€¢ The area is a marine reserve, providing additional protection for marine life.  â€¢ Donsol, Philippines:  â€¢ Whale shark season: November to June.  â€¢ Community-led tourism with strict guidelines to protect the sharks.  â€¢ No feeding or baiting; encounters are in the sharks' natural environment.  â€¢ Tofo Beach, Mozambique:  â€¢ Whale shark season: October to March.  â€¢ Research and conservation efforts support sustainable tourism practices.  â€¢ Encounters are regulated to ensure the well-being of the animals.  â€¢ Dhigurah, Maldives:  â€¢ Whale shark season: Year-round, with a peak from August to November.  â€¢ The Maldives Whale Shark Research Programme promotes ethical tourism and conservation.  â€¢ Strict regulations and community involvement in tourism management.  â€¢ Socorro Island, Mexico:  â€¢ Whale shark season: November to June.  â€¢ The island is part of a protected marine biosphere reserve.  â€¢ Tours are heavily regulated to ensure minimal disruption to marine life.  When choosing a tour operator, look for certifications or affiliations with conservation organizations, adherence to local regulations, and a clear commitment to sustainable practices. This helps ensure that your experience contributes to the protection and preservation of whale sharks and their habitats.  #swimwithwhalesharks  #whalesharkadventure  #EthicalTravel #MarineConservation #sustainabletourism  #whalesharkencounter  #protectouroceans  #OceanConservation  #wildliferespect  #ecofriendlytravel  #marinelifelover  #wildlifephotography  #responsibletravel  #whalesharkseason  #underwaterworld  #savethewhalesharks  #MarineBiodiversity #sustainabletravel  #WhaleShark  #marinewildlife
